Perfect 👍 — since your base URI is now http://localhost:8081/api, here’s a full list of all endpoints and methods you can test from Postman, Anypoint, or browser for the Social Media API.

🌐 Base URI
http://localhost:8081/api

🧍‍♀️ USERS
Method	Endpoint	Description	Request Body (if needed)
GET	/users	Get all users (optional filter by username)	—
GET	/users?username=jdoe	Filter users by username	—
POST	/users	Create a new user	{ "username": "jdoe", "displayName": "John Doe", "bio": "Coffee lover" }
GET	/users/{userId}	Get user by ID	—
GET	/users/{userId}/posts	Get all posts by a specific user	—
POST	/users/{userId}/posts	Create post for that user	{ "content": "Hello world!", "hashtags": ["welcome"] }
📝 POSTS
Method	Endpoint	Description	Request Body (if needed)
GET	/posts	Get all posts	—
GET	/posts?hashtags=travel,food	Filter posts by hashtags	—
GET	/posts?mentions=jdoe,friend1	Filter posts by mentions	—
POST	/posts	Create a new post	{ "authorId": "u_123", "content": "Enjoying the beach!", "hashtags": ["travel"] }
GET	/posts/{postId}	Get a post by ID	—
PUT	/posts/{postId}	Update a post	{ "content": "Updated caption" }
DELETE	/posts/{postId}	Delete a post	—
💬 COMMENTS
Method	Endpoint	Description	Request Body (if needed)
GET	/comments	Get all recent comments	—
GET	/comments/{commentId}	Get comment by ID	—
GET	/posts/{postId}/comments	Get comments for a post	—
POST	/posts/{postId}/comments	Add comment to a post	{ "authorId": "u_222", "content": "Nice post!" }
❤️ LIKES
Method	Endpoint	Description	Request Body (if needed)
GET	/likes	Get all likes	—
POST	/posts/{postId}/likes	Like a post	{ "userId": "u_123" }
DELETE	/posts/{postId}/likes	Unlike a post	—
🧾 QUERY PARAMETERS SUPPORTED
Resource	Parameter	Example	Description
/users	username	/users?username=jdoe	Filter by username
/posts	hashtags	/posts?hashtags=travel,food	Filter posts with specific hashtags
/posts	mentions	/posts?mentions=friend1	Filter posts mentioning a user
/posts	limit & offset	/posts?limit=10&offset=20	Pagination
⚙️ RATE LIMIT HEADERS (Returned in responses)

Each API response may include these headers to indicate your rate limit status:

X-RateLimit-Limit: 100
X-RateLimit-Remaining: 98
X-RateLimit-Reset: 1735660000

🩺 HEALTH CHECK
Method	Endpoint	Description
GET	/health	Quick check if API is running

Example output:

{
  "status": "ok",
  "time": "2025-10-31T00:00:00Z"
}


✅ To Test Quickly in Postman:

Set Base URL: http://localhost:8081/api

Test sequentially:

GET /health

GET /users

POST /users

GET /posts

POST /posts

GET /posts/{id}/comments

POST /posts/{id}/likes
